Good job! your TIR is of 79%


Glucose Management Indicator (Estimated A1C): 6.56



Good meal control but numerous corrections


Your postmeal glycemic control is good, however:

  • You have higher risk of hyperglycemia beyond 2h after meal, suggesting problems with meals rich in protein or fat. Consider using square boluses.
  • On average, you are using 13.7 boluses per day. Please consider refresh your carb ratio and carb measuraments.

Visit counting carb guide help for some guidance.





Sundays are the days with poorest control


Sundays also are the day of the week with highest risk of hypoglycemia, but Saturdays are worse for hyperglycemia.




Worst control happens during the night






Risk of hypoglycemia around noon and afternoons

Beyond the night control, there is a high risk of hypoglycemia between 15h and 18h.
Also, there is a mild risk at 13h and 22h, suggesting mild risk of hypoglycemia before meals. Consider checking your basal insulin.



Afternoon hypoglycemic events tend to be overcorrected

Often, hypoglycemic events between 15 and 18h are overcorrected, leading to a mild hyperglycemia.
